  "prompt": "What marks are required in the IISER aptitude test in order to get admission in any of the IISERs? Also, what rank in the JEE (Advanced) is good enough?",
  "response": "To gain admission to the Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs) through the IISER Aptitude Test (ISAT), candidates typically need to score well to qualify, but there is no fixed cutoff. Admission in recent years has generally depended on relative performance, with higher scores significantly increasing the chances of securing a seat in a preferred IISER.\n\nFor admission through JEE (Advanced), a good rank can vary each year based on the level of competition and the number of seats available. Generally, ranks within the top 10,000 can be competitive for IISER admissions, but candidates should aim for ranks even lower to strengthen their chances.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information regarding cutoffs and admission criteria, it's best to refer to the official IISER admission website or latest notifications from IISERs directly.",
